solution: ```class Solution {
public:
    int distanceTraveled(int mainTank, int additionalTank) {
        int distance = 0;
        while (mainTank > 0) {
            int use = min(mainTank, 5);
            distance += use * 10;
            mainTank -= use;
            if (use == 5 && additionalTank > 0) {
                --additionalTank;
                ++mainTank;
            }
        }
        return distance;
    }
};
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(mainTank)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: Simulate fuel consumption in 5-liter chunks; whenever 5 liters are used and extra fuel exists, transfer 1 liter from the additional tank. Loop ends when main tank is empty.

